Downy mildew on field cucumbers detected in Ontario
----------------------------------------------------
A pickling cucumber field in Ontario [Canada], east of Windsor, was
found to have downy mildew. It is thought that the infection occurred
within the last week. In past years, Michigan [USA] has found its 1st
outbreak 5 to 14 days after an Ontario report. Therefore, Michigan
growers are advised to begin a preventive spray program immediately.
Downy mildew is well-known for causing catastrophic losses in a brief
period of time.

This downy mildew pathogen is resistant to commonly used fungicides.
Results from our 2005-10 research identified a limited number of
fungicides that are effective, but must be applied every 5 days when
the weather favors disease.

[Byline: Mary Hausbeck]

